      "For Blueprint, X-energy complements Oklo: one emphasizes hyperscaler campus deployment with prepayment economics; the other emphasizes licensed HTGR modules, industrial heat, and a qualified domestic fuel pathway. We hold both acknowledging sector execution risk while avoiding single-design bet concentration.",
      "Amazon's multi-gigawatt framework provides demand credibility for investors modeling fuel factory utilization even before first reactor operation—TRISO production becomes a revenue line independent of any single site's construction schedule. Energy Northwest's Washington project illustrates utility-led deployment distinct from industrial heat at Dow Seadrift, diversifying end-market exposure within one reactor design.",
      "Initial public offering capitalization funds the transition from engineering company to serial supplier—a step licensor models must take to meet anchor customer timelines. We selected X-energy when TRISO Category II licensing and Dow permit review converged with public capital markets access in April 2026.",
      "Xe-100 modules ship as factory-built units with TRISO fuel designed for passive safety characteristics regulators evaluate differently from light-water designs—technical differentiation supporting siting conversations with industrial customers unfamiliar with conventional nuclear construction risk. Talen's PJM letter of intent signals grid-connected utility interest beyond hyperscaler and chemical plant anchors already public.",
      "Fuel factory economics may prove as durable as reactor licensing fees if multiple advanced reactor vendors require TRISO supply constrained globally—X-energy's early Category II license creates timing advantage. Blueprint underwrites the combined reactor-plus-fuel story rather than treating X-energy as a single-project developer.",
      "Public listing in April 2026 improves transparency and capital access for long-lead manufacturing—important when anchor customers measure supplier viability in years, not quarters. We added X-energy when fuel licensing and Dow permit progress made the licensor model legible to public investors.",
      "Doosan, IHI, and Curtiss-Wright supply agreements cover reactor pressure vessels, circulators, and core barrels—long-lead items that historically delay nuclear projects when procurement starts late. X-energy's post-IPO focus on simultaneously scaling fuel and components matches the parallel path anchor customers expect from a credible licensor.",
      "PJM capacity markets and data-center load growth in Virginia and adjacent regions contextualize Talen's gigawatt-scale letter of intent—grid-connected modules may complement campus-sited Oklo deployments within Blueprint's diversified nuclear expression. We monitor permit dockets and fuel production metrics as leading indicators, not equity volatility.",
      "Graphite and coated-particle fuel supply chains remain globally constrained; X-energy's vertical integration is a strategic choice to capture margin and de-risk customer schedules when multiple reactor vendors compete for the same suppliers.",
      "Sources: X-energy SEC filing highlights, CNBC initial public offering coverage April 2026, Talen letter-of-intent release, and Nuclear Regulatory Commission fuel licensing documents.",
